-- U.K. Shortlists Four Projects Bidding for $1.6 Billion CCS Funds
-- B y   S a l l y   B a k e w e l l
-- 2012-10-30T09:54:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-30/u-k-shortlists-four-projects-bidding-for-1-6-billion-ccs-funds.html
The U.K. government named four
projects to a shortlist for 1 billion pounds ($1.6 billion) of
funding for  carbon capture  and storage projects.  The Captain Clean Energy project led by Summit Power Group
LLC,  Petrofac Ltd. (PFC) ,  National Grid Plc (NG/)  and  Siemens AG (SIE)  made the
list along with the Peterhead project managed by  Royal Dutch
Shell Plc (RDSA)  and  SSE Plc. (SSE)  The another project named was White Rose,
run by  Drax Group Plc (DRX) , BOC Group Ltd. and National Grid. A
project on Teesside run by  GDF Suez (GSZ)  SA,  Premier Oil Plc (PMO)  and BOC
also made the list.  The list was narrowed from eight bids that submitted
proposals for the funding.  To contact the reporter on this story:
